stories.text:
I am seeing news that companies are putting in place hiring freezes. Some are laying people off, and others are cutting back on hiring.

In your opinion, what skills should one learn today to weather the storm and remain in demand in this challenging job market?
stories.title: Ask HN: Skills in This Tech Job Market?

stories.text: I am currently in the position of interviewing for a few different companies. It's likely that my number 1 choice would be finishing the process later than a couple others which I would take, but only if rejected by the number 1 choice. Is it normal in this space to basically tell a company "I'm waiting on other options", without burning a bridge?
stories.title: Ask HN: How to navigate offers when interviewing with multiple companies?
